    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">László Drakulya to Miklós Oláh (Prague, 11 December 1543)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. László Drakula’s parents told him that he and Oláh
                            shared a grandfather, namely Dracula or Vlad Țepeș, to whom King
                            Matthias married one of his female relatives. This Vlad was famous for
                            his cruelties, and he had three sons, one of whom was Voivode Mihnea,
                            the second was Oláh’s father, and the third was Drakula’s father. 2.
                            After Vlad was killed by the boyars, Mihnea became voivode, and he had
                            60 boyars killed in revenge. After this, he deemed it safe to tell King
                            Vladislaus II everything and offered his Transalpine fortifications to
                            him, in exchange for which the King should give him estates in Hungary.
                            In the end, Jakšić killed Mihnea in Sibiu, and as Oláh knows well, this
                            has harmed them greatly. From all this Oláh can see that their ancestors
                            always had great power and were the allies of the Christian rulers. It
                            would be good if Oláh told all this to the King so that once he rules
                            everything, he should also look after them (Drakula and Oláh).</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Reverendissime Domine, Domine mihi Observandissime!<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">On this letter, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Szilágyi–Nagy</hi> 2022.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Ego enim, quemdamodum a parentibus meis<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.2">His father was Ludovicus Drakula.</note> accepi, vere et
                    ingenue cognationem meam refero, nec aliter se res habet.<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">On the Dracula family, see <hi rend="smallcap">Nagy</hi>
                        2010.</note><persName>Avum</persName> igitur Vestrae Reverendissimae
                        Dominationis<note type="critic" xml:id="note.4">According to Drakulya’s
                        family tree, he was Vlad Țepeș, but László Drakulya is wrong: Vlad was
                        neither Oláh’s grandfather nor ancestor.</note> et
                        <persName>meum</persName><persName>Mathias rex</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">King Mathias I.</note> ceperat et unam cognatam suam <del
                        corresp="Olahus">ei</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">avo meo</add> in
                        <persName>uxorem</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Marina
                        Hunyadi.</note> dedit, sicque ipsum <persName>Wlaad vaidat</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.7">Vlad Țepeș.</note> nomine Ladislaum avum
                    nostrum in vaivodatum Transalpinum miserat, eique contulit. Nominatus autem
                    nomine hoc Drakulya ob nimiam ipsius crudelitatem fuit, quod super ipsum ad
                    extremum vitae suae diem usque permansit. Ipse igitur avus noster
                        <persName>Wlaad vaida</persName><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">sive
                        Dracula</add> tres filios habuit, quorum unus fuit <persName>Myhne
                        vaida</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.8">Mihnea cel Rău.</note>
                    secundus vero <persName>pater</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.9"
                        >István Oláh, see <hi rend="smallcap">Dörner</hi> 1994; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Szilágyi</hi> 2021.</note> Vestrae Reverendissimae
                    Dominationis, tertius autem pater meus nomine <persName>Ludovicus Drakulya
                        vaida</persName>, et quia nimis crudelis fuit, eam ob rem a boieris
                    trucidatus fuit, et sic posteri ipsius huc devenerunt. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Cum autem <persName>Myhne vaida</persName> denuo ad vaivodatum
                    vocatus fuit, ex voluntate patris Vestrae Reverendissimae Dominationis et mei ad
                    officium vaivodatus profectus fuit. Hinc itaque Vestra Reverendissima Dominatio
                    facile coniicere potest et diiudicare, nos circa regnum illud iustitiam habere,
                        <persName>Myhne</persName> igitur vaida ob interitum
                        <persName>avi</persName> nostri, simul et semel 60 boiaros occidi et
                    trucidari iussit. Peracta igitur crudelitate, persuasum habens se rem impune non
                    laturum, omne suum negotium cum <persName>rege Ladislao</persName> contulit et
                    communicavit medio <persName>Petri Groffh</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.10">Péter of Szentgyörgy and Bazin (1498–1510) was Voivode of
                        Transsylvania between 1498 and 1510, see <hi rend="smallcap">C.
                            Tóth–Horváth–Neumann–Pálosfalvi</hi> 2017, 88.</note> vaivoda
                    Transylvaniensem tunc existentem, ut scilicet ipse <persName>Myhne</persName>
                    munitiones Transalpinenses ad manus regis daret, rexque ei pro bonis ipsius in
                    Hungaria alia bona ut conferret. Quomodo vero ipsum
                        <persName>Myhne</persName><persName>Demetrius Iaxyth</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.11">Dmitar
                        Jakšić.</note><placeName>Cibinii</placeName> fraudulenter ferro confodi
                        iussit,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.12">See Ep. 333. and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Szilágyi</hi> 2018,
                        427.<ref>olahus.tei.15330307_1</ref></note> id Vestram Reverendissimam
                    Dominationem latere non opinor. Cuius quidem interitus nobis omnibus male assit,
                    negotium igitur istud a domino Matheo<note type="critic" xml:id="note.13">Máté
                        Oláh.</note> quoque fratre Vestrae Reverendissimae Dominationis tali ordine
                    accepi et ita, ut audivi, vere refero, cuius rei memoriam Vestra Reverendissima
                    Dominatio forsan habere potest. Bene igitur iam Vestra Reverendissima Dominatio
                    intelliget, quod <milestone unit="pb"/>regnum illud antecessores nostri magna
                    cum potentia semper obtinuerunt et <choice>
                        <orig>possederunt</orig>
                        <supplied>possiderunt</supplied>
                    </choice> semperque cum Christianis principibus coniuncti fuerunt. Bonum igitur
                    esset, si Vestra Reverendissima Dominatio nacta occasione rem istam sacrae
                    regiae maiestati exponeret, nam mihi quidem magna fiducia est, quod regia
                    maiestas, volente Deo, omne suum imperium obtinebit et sic forsitan de nobis
                    quoque provideretur. </p>
                <pb/>
